 -- Leonid Borisenko <leo.borisenko@gmail.com>  Thu, 10 Mar 2011 04:56:13 +0200

uwsgi (0.9.6.8-0ubuntu1~uwsgimaintppa1~maverick1) maverick; urgency=low

  * New upstream release.
  * Remove uwsgi binary package.
  * Transform uwsgi-python2.6 and uwsgi-python3.1 binary packages into
    transitional dummy packages. Note, that now they can be safely removed from
    system.
  * Provide functionality of uwsgi-python2.6 and uwsgi-python3.1 packages with
    (respectively) uwsgi-python and uwsgi-python3:
    - each of uwsgi-pythonX packages contains executables named uwsgi-pythonX.Y
      for all packaged pythonX.Y versions
    - uwsgi-python and uwsgi-python3 executables are provided by alternatives
      system. By default, they are symlinked to uwsgi-pythonX.Y executables,
      where X.Y is default pythonX version
    - move directory for configuration files from /etc/uwsgi/uwsgi-pythonX.Y to
      /etc/uwsgi-pythonX/{apps-available,apps-enabled}. See README in new
      configuration subdirectories for description of their's purposes
    - move defaults file from /etc/default/pythonX.Y to
      /etc/default/uwsgi-pythonX
    - move runtime directory from /var/run/uwsgi/uwsgi-pythonX.Y to
      /var/run/uwsgi-pythonX
    - move log directory from /var/log/uwsgi/uwsgi-pythonX.Y to
      /var/log/uwsgi-pythonX
  * Add .rtupdate script to uwsgi-pythonX packages for updating of alternative
    system symlink of uwsgi-pythonX executable on default pythonX version
    changing (but only if alternative group is in automatic mode).
  * Add python-django-uwsgi-admin package with uwsgi_admin Django application
    from uWSGI distribution.
  * Add uwsgi-plugins-all dependency package for installing all packaged
    uWSGI plugins at once.
  * Add uwsgi-python-dbg and uwsgi-python3-dbg packages with debug symbols for
    uwsgi-pythonX.Y executables.
  * Extend starting/controlling of uWSGI instances in init.d script with
    support for YAML configuration files (.yaml/.yml extensions are
    recognized).
  * Fix error in handling of configuration files by init.d script. Now, all
    configuration files are processed (not only the first found).
    Closes LP: #713479
  * Handle weird configuration file names (those with spaces and/or control
    characters).
  * Print one-character symbols instead of configuration file names in init.d
    script output. Old behavior could be enabled by setting in
    /etc/default/uwsgi-pythonX file.
  * Update README.Debian of uwsgi-pythonX packages.
  * Bump debhelper compatibility level (from 7 to 8) with no changes.
  * Update debian/copyright to most current DEP-5 version.
  * Add python to Build-Depends for getting dh_python2 helper (as Lintian
    suggests).
  * Add Stephen Crosby to Uploaders.

 -- Leonid Borisenko <leo.borisenko@gmail.com>  Thu, 10 Mar 2011 02:58:28 +0200

